Standard Bank Hires from JPMorgan, Investec to Bolster Securities Business

-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 
2011-02-22T08:57:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-22/standard-bank-hires-from-jpmorgan-investec-to-bolster-securities-unit.html
  Standard Bank  Group Ltd. said its
SBG Securities unit made appointments to boost the number of its
Johannesburg-based analysts to 12.  SBG Securities appointed Ross Elliot of JPMorgan Chase &
Co. for equity sales, Jonathan Kennedy-Good of Investec Ltd.’s
securities business as a telecommunications analyst and head of
coverage for technology, media and telecommunications, Standard
Bank said in an e-mailed statement today.  Jennifer Henry was appointed from  Nedbank Group Ltd .’s
securities business to help media, electronics and information
technology coverage while Monique Swartz joins as a resources
strategist, it said. Adriaan Du Toit will be head of South
African economics research and Hennie Loubser was named as a
small- and mid-cap analyst.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vernon Wessels at 
 vwessels@bloomberg.net  